{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1063,"text":"The child's symptoms begin"},{"time":3295,"text":"with mild fever, headache, muscle pains,"},{"time":6956,"text":"followed by vomiting and diarrhea,"},{"time":9067,"text":"then bleeding from the mouth,\nnose and gums."},{"time":13603,"text":"Death follows in the form of organ failure\nfrom low blood pressure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19887,"text":"Sounds familiar?"},{"time":21592,"text":"If you're thinking this is Ebola,"},{"time":24215,"text":"actually, in this case, it's not."},{"time":26576,"text":"It's an extreme form of dengue fever,\na mosquito-born disease"},{"time":31955,"text":"which also does not have\nan effective therapy or a vaccine,"},{"time":36040,"text":"and kills 22,000 people each year."},{"time":40018,"text":"That is actually twice\nthe number of people"},{"time":42918,"text":"that have been killed by Ebola"},{"time":44971,"text":"in the nearly four decades\nthat we've known about it."},{"time":48740,"text":"As for measles, so much\nin the news recently,"},{"time":52463,"text":"the death toll is actually tenfold higher."},{"time":57578,"text":"Yet for the last year,"},{"time":59373,"text":"it has been Ebola that has stolen\nall of the headlines and the fear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65059,"text":"Clearly, there is something\ndeeply rooted about it,"},{"time":67880,"text":"something which scares us\nand fascinates us"},{"time":70783,"text":"more than other diseases."},{"time":72896,"text":"But what is it, exactly?"},{"time":75357,"text":"Well, it's hard to acquire Ebola,"},{"time":77610,"text":"but if you do, the risk\nof a horrible death is high."},{"time":81697,"text":"Why?"},{"time":82873,"text":"Because right now, we don't have any\neffective therapy or vaccine available."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88133,"text":"And so, that's the clue."},{"time":91022,"text":"We may have it someday."},{"time":93453,"text":"So we rightfully fear Ebola,"},{"time":96804,"text":"because it doesn't kill\nas many people as other diseases."},{"time":101246,"text":"In fact, it's much less transmissible\nthan viruses such as flu or measles."},{"time":107270,"text":"We fear Ebola because of the fact\nthat it kills us and we can't treat it."},{"time":113112,"text":"We fear the certain inevitability\nthat comes with Ebola."},{"time":116524,"text":"Ebola has this inevitability\nthat seems to defy modern medical science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122507,"text":"But wait a second, why is that?"},{"time":124705,"text":"We've known about Ebola since 1976."},{"time":128036,"text":"We've known what it's capable of."},{"time":130132,"text":"We've had ample opportunity to study it"},{"time":132786,"text":"in the 24 outbreaks that have occurred."},{"time":135491,"text":"And in fact, we've actually had\nvaccine candidates available now"},{"time":139991,"text":"for more than a decade."},{"time":141856,"text":"Why is that those vaccines\nare just going into clinical trials now?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":146930,"text":"This goes to the fundamental\nproblem we have"},{"time":149788,"text":"with vaccine development\nfor infectious diseases."},{"time":153197,"text":"It goes something like this:"},{"time":155983,"text":"The people most at risk for these diseases"},{"time":158810,"text":"are also the ones least able\nto pay for vaccines."},{"time":163858,"text":"This leaves little in the way\nof market incentives"},{"time":167281,"text":"for manufacturers to develop vaccines,"},{"time":170269,"text":"unless there are large numbers of people\nwho are at risk in wealthy countries."},{"time":175522,"text":"It's simply too commercially risky."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179244,"text":"As for Ebola, there is absolutely\nno market at all,"},{"time":183432,"text":"so the only reason we have two vaccines\nin late-stage clinical trials now,"},{"time":189084,"text":"is actually because\nof a somewhat misguided fear."},{"time":192520,"text":"Ebola was relatively ignored"},{"time":195768,"text":"until September 11\nand the anthrax attacks,"},{"time":200333,"text":"when all of a sudden,\npeople perceived Ebola"},{"time":202891,"text":"as, potentially, a bioterrorism weapon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205485,"text":"Why is it that the Ebola vaccine\nwasn't fully developed at this point?"},{"time":210167,"text":"Well, partially, because\nit was really difficult --"},{"time":212787,"text":"or thought to be difficult --\nto weaponize the virus,"},{"time":215460,"text":"but mainly because\nof the financial risk in developing it."},{"time":221028,"text":"And this is really the point."},{"time":223718,"text":"The sad reality is, we develop vaccines"},{"time":226262,"text":"not based upon the risk\nthe pathogen poses to people,"},{"time":230158,"text":"but on how economically risky it is\nto develop these vaccines."},{"time":234887,"text":"Vaccine development\nis expensive and complicated."},{"time":237820,"text":"It can cost hundreds\nof millions of dollars"},{"time":239915,"text":"to take even a well-known antigen\nand turn it into a viable vaccine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245001,"text":"Fortunately for diseases like Ebola,"},{"time":247479,"text":"there are things we can do\nto remove some of these barriers."},{"time":251385,"text":"The first is to recognize\nwhen there's a complete market failure."},{"time":255314,"text":"In that case, if we want vaccines,"},{"time":258372,"text":"we have to provide incentives\nor some type of subsidy."},{"time":264197,"text":"We also need to do a better job\nat being able to figure out"},{"time":268561,"text":"which are the diseases\nthat most threaten us."},{"time":271260,"text":"By creating capabilities within countries,\nwe then create the ability"},{"time":276199,"text":"for those countries to create\nepidemiological and laboratory networks"},{"time":280840,"text":"which are capable of collecting\nand categorizing these pathogens."},{"time":286117,"text":"The data from that then can be used"},{"time":288403,"text":"to understand the geographic\nand genetic diversity,"},{"time":291706,"text":"which then can be used\nto help us understand"},{"time":294366,"text":"how these are being changed\nimmunologically,"},{"time":298033,"text":"and what type of reactions they promote."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301198,"text":"So these are the things that can be done,"},{"time":303549,"text":"but to do this, if we want to deal\nwith a complete market failure,"},{"time":307257,"text":"we have to change the way\nwe view and prevent infectious diseases."},{"time":312705,"text":"We have to stop waiting\nuntil we see evidence"},{"time":316916,"text":"of a disease becoming a global threat\nbefore we consider it as one."},{"time":322617,"text":"So, for Ebola,"},{"time":324880,"text":"the paranoid fear\nof an infectious disease,"},{"time":328795,"text":"followed by a few cases\ntransported to wealthy countries,"},{"time":333541,"text":"led the global community to come together,"},{"time":336165,"text":"and with the work\nof dedicated vaccine companies,"},{"time":339694,"text":"we now have these:"},{"time":342465,"text":"Two Ebola vaccines in efficacy trials\nin the Ebola countries --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":348496,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":354025,"text":"and a pipeline of vaccines\nthat are following behind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358763,"text":"Every year, we spend billions of dollars,"},{"time":361879,"text":"keeping a fleet of nuclear submarines\npermanently patrolling the oceans"},{"time":366976,"text":"to protect us from a threat\nthat almost certainly will never happen."},{"time":371527,"text":"And yet, we spend virtually nothing"},{"time":374487,"text":"to prevent something as tangible\nand evolutionarily certain"},{"time":379538,"text":"as epidemic infectious diseases."},{"time":383009,"text":"And make no mistake about it --\nit's not a question of \"if,\" but \"when.\""},{"time":386928,"text":"These bugs are going to continue to evolve"},{"time":389864,"text":"and they're going to threaten the world."},{"time":392280,"text":"And vaccines are our best defense."},{"time":395108,"text":"So if we want to be able to prevent\nepidemics like Ebola,"},{"time":399441,"text":"we need to take on the risk\nof investing in vaccine development"},{"time":403911,"text":"and in stockpile creation."},{"time":406760,"text":"And we need to view this, then,\nas the ultimate deterrent --"},{"time":410409,"text":"something we make sure is available,"},{"time":413553,"text":"but at the same time,\npraying we never have to use it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417621,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418796,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}